Privacy Policy
10/27/2022
DalcomSoft Japan, Inc. (“DalcomSoft Japan”, “we”, “our” or “us”) handles collection, use and sharing of information based on this Privacy Policy (“Privacy Policy”) in connection with the application provided by DalcomSoft Japan and any associated services provided with it (collectively, “Services”). DalcomSoft Japan may change this Privacy Policy from time to time. In certain cases, DalcomSoft Japan may also give you additional notice of the changes such as by displaying a statement on our homepage, mobile applications and/or Services. Unless specifically indicated otherwise, any changes to this Privacy Policy shall become effective at the time the revised Privacy Policy is posted on this website.
We encourage you to review the Privacy Policy whenever you access the Services to stay informed of our information practices and the ways you can protect your privacy.
1. Collection of Information
DalcomSoft Japan will collect and process the following information during your use our services.
1.1
Information for signing in to our Service
(1) Identity-related data(Name, Username, screen name, Birthday, and/or Age
(2) e-mail address
(3) Username and/or password to sign in to our Services
(4) Public profile information connected SNS(Profile Photo, Username, Gender, Career and so. )
(5) Any other information you choose to provide directly to DalcomSoft Japan.
1.2
Information for you participate in events and campaigns
(1) Identity-related data(Name, Address, Phone number, Age, Birthday, Gender, e-mail address and so.)
1.3
Information to provide user support
(1) Contact information(Name, e-mail address and so.)
(2) Device information(Device model, OS platform and version)
(3) Data about your activities on Services
(4) Account information(User ID, Username and Password)
1.4
Information for analytics
(1) Your activities in Services information(Cookies, IP address, e-mail address and so.)
(2) Device information(Device model, OS platform and version)
(3) Data about your activities on Services from tracking technology
1.5
Information of your location
(1) Device location information(IP address)
1.6
Information of your devices
(1) Device information(Device ID, IP Address, OS platform and version)
1.7
Information of Payment
(1) Information of charge and/or invoice which you provide payment-collection service agent, subject that you purchase in-game currency and/or other items through the agent.
1.8
Information linked with other services
(1) Information of your ID and/or other information which you used and authorized to disclose to other service agency for linking with the service or/and log-in authentication(i.e. Facebook or/and Google account).
1.9
If you are under GDPR or the equivalent laws, DalcomSoft Japan request your consent to allow DalcomSoft Japan to manage the information above when you get started to use Services. If you do not agree with the request, you may not be able to use Services.
2. Information Collected by Cookies and Other Tracking Technologies:
2.1
DalcomSoft Japan use various technologies to collect information and these technologies may include sending cookies to your computer or mobile device. Cookies are small data files stored on your hard drive or in your device memory that (i) help DalcomSoft Japan improve our Services and your experience, (ii) identify the areas and features of Services that are popular and (iii) count visits relating to our Services. For more information about cookies and how to disable them, please see “3.Purpose of using your information” below. DalcomSoft Japan may also collect information using web beacons (also known as tracking pixels), which are electronic images that may be used in our Services and emails. Web beacons help us (i) deliver cookies, (ii) count visits, (iii) understand the utility and effectiveness of campaigns and (iv) determine whether an email has been opened and acted upon.
2.2
Other Information Collected with Permission: Our mobile applications that are distributed through the Google Play store and the Apple App Store may also request for your permission to automatically collect other information from your mobile device including your email address. DalcomSoft Japan may only collect this information with your authorization given in accordance with the permission process of your device operating system.
3. Purpose of using your information
DalcomSoft Japan will use your information for the following purposes.
(1) To provide you DalcomSoft Japan Services and update
(2) To monitor and ban suspicious and/or unexpected use
(3) To analyze user activities in Services for developing and improving
(4) To communicate with you for customer services and/or inquiry
(5) To provide Information about update, campaign, administrative messages and so
(6) To propose you targeted and relevant advertisements and analyze effect of the advertisements
(7) To provide you with benefits/prizes
(8) To confirm user identification for campaign, customer support and so
(9) To calculate and charge using Services fee.
(10) To manage in-game currency, points, virtual currency, and so.
(11) To notify when DalcomSoft Japan perform Services system maintenance and/or revising Privacy Policy or other term and condition to you
4. Legal basis for use of your information
If you are in GDPR area, DalcomSoft Japan use your information in the following Legal Basis
(1) You have provided us with your consent to do so.
(2) DalcomSoft Japan need use your information to perform our obligations under any contract with you
(3) DalcomSoft Japan need comply with a legal obligation to which DalcomSoft Japan is subject
(4) DalcomSoft Japan need protect the vital interests of the data subject or of another natural person
(5) DalcomSoft Japan need perform a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in DalcomSoft Japan
(6) DalcomSoft Japan or third parties need pursue the legitimate interests, except where such interests are overridden by the interests or fundamental rights and freedoms of the data subject which require protection of personal data, in particular where the data subject is a child.
※(6)shall not apply to processing carried out by public authorities in the performance of their tasks.
5. Sharing of Information
DalcomSoft Japan may share information that DalcomSoft Japan have collected about you in the following manners or as otherwise specified in this Privacy Policy with the following vendors, consultants and other service providers who require access to the information to carry out work on our behalf.
(1)Google:
